<plot>Two people find themselves locked in the trunk of a car with no means of escape, frustrated by the ambivalent nature of their captor(s). "alone" is an exploration into our limited understanding of a "greater power". Designed to offend and entertain, descended from the works of preceding Dadaist and Existentialists, "alone" is a unique ride of a man and woman's journey towards personal understanding.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?032489</url></doc>
